title: It puts knowledge* into a geometry.
pid: add70639-7bd9-46ab-b0d9-6f8901cdd5a8
body: |2-
    * Knowledge, notes, information, data, writing, thought(s) -- in knowledge graph software, they are nearly synonyms.

    Building a geometry on knowledge is not new.
    If you want to know why it helps,
    please, talk to an enthusiast of
    'knowledge base' or 'knowledge graph' software
    like Notion, logseq, org-roam, Semantic Synchrony,
    Roam, Obsidian, Tana, or many others.
